==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crown-saw
<hw>Crown"-saw`</hw> <pr>(-s?`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From its
supposed resemblance to a <ets>crown</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mech.)</fld>
<def>A saw in the form of a hollow cylinder, with teeth on the end or
edge, and operated by a rotative motion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The trephine was the first of the class of
crownsaws.</note> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crown side</ent>⟦br⟧
